\n<Marion>...Why do you ask about that name?

\n<Marion>That's absurd. Ruin was creating something called a
Manoloid?

\n<Marion>To begin with, ever since I completed the modified girl,
he's been completely out of touch.
\n<Marion>So, I had assumed he died from the monster damage...
\n<Marion>...Well, at least I thought we were.
\n<Marion>Then, let me read that letter or whatever it is.
You and I were good friends, both aspiring to be engineers.

But it was always only you whose achievements were
recognized.

All of my discoveries at that time were condemned as
dangerous and discarded.

While I couldn't succeed in anything, you somehow completed
the modified girl who would save the world.
I still remember that moment even now.

Crushed by a sense of inferiority, I thought I never wanted
to see you again.

Even after the modified girl was defeated once and the world
was dominated by monsters, I continued to live in hiding.
...A few months after the original monster was defeated,

I met someone for the first time who acknowledged my
technology.
I followed that person and continued to create Manoloids.

My Manoloids will one day defeat the modified girl you
created.
With that sole purpose, I became an ally of the monsters.
Seeing me as I am now, what do you think?
\n<Marion>...So, Eury defeated that Manoloid or whatever it was.

\n<Marion>But that alone wasn't enough reason not to turn into a
monster...
\n<Eury>...He said he was in Tengeki Street.
\n<Marion>Sorry, but I can't go there. Find him and bring him here!

\n<Marion>Creating monsters is an act too dangerous to be dismissed as
mere terrorism. He needs to wake up soon...!

\n<Makina>By the way, there's a forest near Tengeki Street. It seems
there was a reaction from a large demon there.

\n<Makina>Can you patrol during the daytime? If there are any
suspicious traces, we'll need to go defeat it at night.

\n<Makina>Take this with you, you can't fight if you run out of
bullets.

\n<Makina>I have my own mission. I'm operating from a different town,
but the situation is urgent.

\n<Makina>Sorry, but I must go now. Eury, be sure to take on your
mission without any negligence.

\n<Makina>...If you lose to the demon, who knows what will happen.
Eury, really, don't push yourself too hard.
\n<Marion>Hey Ruin, why did you side with the monsters?
\n<Ruin>...I wrote about it in the letter.

\n<Marion>I understand that it's not all about jealousy or an
inferiority complex.

\n<Marion>You're not stupid enough to betray humans just for that
reason, are you?
